Why, the undisputed fact, the fact which every man except a fool admits, that Rome is the work of the gods, and this proves that the Romans taught the philosophers. I do not admit that the writer had the least idea that he was talking this nonsense; but like many others he writes one thing and sup- poses that he is writing another.
